name: Remember to look around
description: Last night I was on my home from the park where’d I’d been sketching and chilling for a couple hours. It had been another long day and the outdoors was doing me well. Suddenly I stopped, took a deep breath, and looked around. I get lost in my own head a lot thinking and because of that I miss a lot. I’ve been trying to get better, but it’s hard. When you’re focused so laser sharp, and and pushing so hard to make something happen…it’s easy to forget. So this picture was my reminder. And a thank you to @captainstax for encouraging me to mint this. They reminded me to practice what I preach and mint what I make. :) Wessel ‘21
